.TH DAEDALUS 1 "2026-03-07" "daedalus 0.8.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
daedalus \- Docker environment for autonomous Claude Code
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B daedalus
[\fIflags\fR] <\fIproject-name\fR> [\fIproject-dir\fR]
.br
.B daedalus list
.br
.B daedalus prune
.br
.B daedalus remove
<\fIname\fR> [\fIname\fR...]
.br
.B daedalus config
<\fIname\fR> [\fB\-\-set\fR \fIkey=value\fR] [\fB\-\-unset\fR \fIkey\fR]
.br
.B daedalus tui
.br
.B daedalus web
[\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB\-\-host\fR \fIHOST\fR]
.br
.B daedalus completion
<\fBbash\fR|\fBzsh\fR|\fBfish\fR>
.br
.B daedalus \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B daedalus
wraps Claude Code in a Docker container with
.B \-\-dangerously\-skip\-permissions\fR,
providing isolation instead of interactive permission prompts.
The container boundary replaces per-action approval with a single trust
decision: Claude can do anything inside the container.
.PP
Each project gets its own named container with the project directory
mounted read-write at
.I /workspace
and a persistent home directory at
.IR /home/claude .
Sessions are wrapped in tmux for detach/reattach support.
.PP
Three UI surfaces are provided: a command-line interface (CLI), an
interactive terminal dashboard (TUI), and a browser-based web dashboard
with an embedded terminal.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
<\fIproject-name\fR>
Open a registered project using its stored directory.
.TP
<\fIproject-name\fR> <\fIproject-dir\fR>
Register a new project and open it. The directory is stored in the registry for future use.
.TP
\fBlist\fR
List all registered projects with their directories, targets, session counts, and last-used timestamps.
.TP
\fBprune\fR
Remove registry entries whose project directories no longer exist on disk. Prompts for confirmation in interactive mode; use \fB\-\-force\fR for non-interactive mode.
.TP
\fBremove\fR <\fIname\fR> [\fIname\fR...]
Remove one or more named projects from the registry. Prompts for confirmation in interactive mode; use \fB\-\-force\fR for non-interactive mode.
.TP
\fBconfig\fR <\fIname\fR> [\fB\-\-set\fR \fIkey=value\fR] [\fB\-\-unset\fR \fIkey\fR]
View or edit per-project default flags. Without \fB\-\-set\fR or \fB\-\-unset\fR, displays the current configuration.
.TP
\fBtui\fR
Launch the interactive terminal dashboard for managing all registered projects. Key bindings: j/Down move down, k/Up move up, s start, a attach, K kill, r refresh, q quit.
.TP
\fBweb\fR [\fB\-\-port\fR \fIPORT\fR] [\fB\-\-host\fR \fIHOST\fR]
Start the browser-based web dashboard with project management and an embedded terminal. Default: localhost:3000.
.TP
\fBcompletion\fR <\fBbash\fR|\fBzsh\fR|\fBfish\fR>
Print a shell completion script to stdout. Source the output in your shell profile.
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Show the usage message and exit.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-build\fR
Force rebuild the Docker image before starting the container.
.TP
\fB\-\-target\fR \fIstage\fR
Docker build target stage. Available targets: \fBdev\fR (default), \fBgodot\fR, \fBbase\fR, \fButils\fR.
.TP
\fB\-\-resume\fR \fIid\fR
Resume a previous Claude Code session by its session ID.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR \fIprompt\fR
Run a headless single-prompt task. The container executes the prompt and exits without interactive input.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-tmux\fR
Run without tmux session wrapping. The container runs directly in the current terminal.
.TP
\fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable Claude Code debug mode.
.TP
\fB\-\-dind\fR
Mount the host Docker socket into the container. WARNING: this grants the container full access to the host Docker daemon.
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
Force deletion in non-interactive mode for \fBprune\fR and \fBremove\fR commands.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable colored output. Also honors the \fBNO_COLOR\fR environment variable.
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fIport\fR
Port for the web UI server. Default: 3000.
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fIhost\fR
Host address for the web UI server to bind to. Default: 127.0.0.1.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBDAEDALUS_DATA_DIR\fR
Base directory for the project registry and per-project caches. Defaults to
.I .cache
next to the daedalus binary.
.TP
\fBNO_COLOR\fR
When set (to any value), disables colored output. See https://no-color.org/.
.SH CONFIGURATION
A JSON configuration file can be placed at
.I <install-dir>/config.json
(default:
.IR ~/.local/share/daedalus/config.json ).
All fields are optional.
.PP
Precedence (highest to lowest): CLI flags, environment variables, config.json, built-in defaults.
.PP
Supported fields:
.TP
\fBdata-dir\fR (string)
Base directory for registry and per-project caches. Must be an absolute path.
.TP
\fBdebug\fR (bool)
Enable Claude Code debug mode.
.TP
\fBno-tmux\fR (bool)
Run without tmux session wrapping.
.TP
\fBimage-prefix\fR (string)
Docker image prefix. Default: techdelight/claude-runner.
.SH EXAMPLES
Open an existing project from the registry:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus my\-app
.fi
.RE
.PP
Register a new project with a directory:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus my\-app /path/to/project
.fi
.RE
.PP
Run a headless single-prompt task:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus my\-app \-p "Fix all linting errors"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Force rebuild with a specific target:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus \-\-build \-\-target godot my\-game /path/to/game
.fi
.RE
.PP
Start the web UI on a custom port:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus web \-\-port 8080
.fi
.RE
.PP
Set per-project defaults:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus config my\-app \-\-set dind=true
.fi
.RE
.PP
Generate and source shell completions:
.PP
.RS
.nf
eval "$(daedalus completion bash)"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Resume a previous Claude session:
.PP
.RS
.nf
daedalus \-\-resume <session\-id> my\-app
.fi
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
Success.
.TP
\fB1\fR
An error occurred (invalid arguments, Docker failure, missing project, etc.).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I <install-dir>/config.json
Application configuration file. See \fBCONFIGURATION\fR above.
.TP
.I .cache/projects.json
Project registry file containing all registered projects, their directories, targets, session history, and timestamps.
.TP
.I .cache/<project>/
Per-project persistent home directory, bind-mounted as \fI/home/claude\fR inside the container. Stores shell history, Claude session transcripts, tool caches, and per-project MCP/settings overrides.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR docker (1),
.BR tmux (1),
.BR claude (1)
